30/11/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- High Representative Miroslav Lajcak is consulting with party leaders about the ongoing institutional crisis, his press office announced on Thursday (November 29th).
Lajcak met with Bosniak leaders Haris Silajdzic and Sulejman Tihic on Wednesday, and with Republika Srspka Prime Minister Milorad Dodik on Thursday.
Serb politicians have threatened to boycott parliament and other institutions over measures Lajcak proposed on October 19th, including amended rules regarding quorums.
He gave local leaders until December 1st.
"Six weeks have been wasted," he said Thursday.
(Nezavisne Novine, Dnevni Avaz - 30/11/07;
RTRS, NTV Hayat, OHR website - 29/11/07)
